        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Cryolite is produced at four sites in the EU-15. 3 of them updated their information in 2006. The production volume of these four sites is 23,561 t/y. 

Assumptions:
- Based on online information found from the specified european production sites related to production means ( Fluorsid, Derivados del Fluor S.A. , I.C.I.B. S.p.A., Solvay Fluor und Derivate) it is estimated that 3/4 of cryolite are produced from HF and 1/4 from fluosilicic acid.

- The production volume is assumed to be similar in 2006 and 2005 (reference year is 2005)

- The World production is extrapolated with the GDP adjustment factor: 3.32 (unit of GDP: current $; World Bank, year 2005). The adjustment factor is the ratio of World GDP/EU GDP

Note: the  production volume has been cross-checked with the amount of cryolite consumption during aluminium manufacture. 2g of cryolite are used for producing 1 kg of Aluminium. Asuming 1/4 of the total cryolite is being produced from fluosilicic acid, the resulting amount is 1.6E7 which is similar to our calculated value.
</productionVolumeComment>
